Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.57,0:00:12.57,Gintama,OP Card,0000,0000,0000,,Gintama
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.45,0:00:12.57,Slip Arc,OP Card,0000,0000,0000,,Slip Arc
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.68,0:01:43.08,Main,Gin,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Gintama Rumble{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.08,0:01:45.10,Main,Gin,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}What the heck is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.10,0:01:51.11,Warning,Warning,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(500,540)}Enjoy {\i1}Gintama Rumble{\i0} in a bright room and at a safe distance from your TV!!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.10,0:01:48.89,Main,Shin,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}What do you mean? It's an upcoming game.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.89,0:01:51.48,Main,Shin,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Following the success of \Nthe {\i1}Gintama{\i0} board game,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.48,0:01:54.47,Main,Shin,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Bandai Namco went all-out to \Nmake another game adaptation.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.47,0:01:58.58,Main,Kag,0000,0000,0000,,And it's an actual action game this time, \Nas you can tell from the "Rumble."
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.58,0:02:00.97,Main,Kag,0000,0000,0000,,It's got tons more money invested\Nin it than the board game.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.97,0:02:05.83,Main,Gin,0000,0000,0000,,What's the point of making an action game \Nwhen we don't have any special moves?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.83,0:02:07.58,Main,Gin,0000,0000,0000,,Talk about living in denial.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.58,0:02:10.19,Main,Gin,0000,0000,0000,,At least it was kinda cute when they \Nmade the board game in desperation.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.19,0:02:11.48,Main,Shin,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, quit complaining.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.48,0:02:15.74,Main,Gin,0000,0000,0000,,What's even going on with the rights? \NDon't you think this is weird, Bamco?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.48,0:02:21.49,sign_2985_16_missing,,0000,0000,0000,,Sugar Content
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.74,0:02:19.55,Main,Shin,0000,0000,0000,,Our protagonist discussing our \Ngame is weirder, if you ask me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.55,0:02:21.49,Main,Gin,0000,0000,0000,,True, we never really talked about it before.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.49,0:02:26.95,Main,Gin,0000,0000,0000,,Regardless of who made games about \Nus or how badly they bombed,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.95,0:02:28.22,Main,Gin,0000,0000,0000,,we pretended not to notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.22,0:02:30.75,Main,Shin,0000,0000,0000,,Stop being rude, or we'll \Nnever get another game!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.29,0:02:34.85,Main,Gin,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, the licensed-game genre has \Nalways been a hotbed of shitty games.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.85,0:02:37.26,Main,Shin,0000,0000,0000,,They're not shitty! They're \Nmade with love and affection!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.26,0:02:44.70,Main,Gin,0000,0000,0000,,But if we don't produce a hit soon, sponsors \Nmight give up on the whole franchise.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.70,0:02:47.90,Main,Gin,0000,0000,0000,,That could lead to a reduction of \Ncross-media promotions and merch
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.90,0:02:49.83,Main,Gin,0000,0000,0000,,and ultimately affect even the anime.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.83,0:02:51.65,Main,Shin,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, the anime isn't really one to talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.07,0:02:56.44,Main,Gin,0000,0000,0000,,Talk about reckless, making an action game \Nwhile we weren't paying attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.44,0:02:59.03,Main,Gin,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be in the bargain bin \Nwithin a few months, no doubt.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.03,0:03:02.28,Main,Shin,0000,0000,0000,,Don't jinx it before the release! \NIt's gonna sell like hotcakes!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.28,0:03:04.48,Main,Gin,0000,0000,0000,,I dunno about other Jump protags,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.48,0:03:08.55,Main,Gin,0000,0000,0000,,but as an adult protag, I'm gonna \Npoint out problems when I see them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.55,0:03:10.00,Main,Shin,0000,0000,0000,,You're the biggest problem here!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.00,0:03:13.67,Main,Shin,0000,0000,0000,,I've never heard of a protag \Nmeddling in his franchise's merch!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.67,0:03:17.51,Main,Gin,0000,0000,0000,,I'm saying I can't just sit back \Nand let Bamco handle it all.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.51,0:03:22.18,Main,Gin,0000,0000,0000,,In this day and age, any protag worth \Nhis salt has to oversee all the merch.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.70,0:03:24.18,Main,Gin,0000,0000,0000,,On that note...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.18,0:03:30.19,Ep Title,Title,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(485,1)}The Line Between Godlike Games \Nand Shitty Games Is Paper-Thin
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.19,0:03:31.94,sign_4872_42_Bandai_Namco,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Bandai Namco
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.94,0:03:34.94,sign_4914_43_Lab_A,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Lab A
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.72,0:03:34.94,Main,Tama,0000,0000,0000,,Main system successfully infiltrated.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.94,0:03:36.07,sign_4986_45_missing,,0000,0000,0000,,Authenticating
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.07,0:03:37.30,sign_5013_46_Unlocked,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1,417)}Unlocked
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.56,0:03:40.61,Main,Tama,0000,0000,0000,,Hacking complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.61,0:03:44.05,Main,Gin,0000,0000,0000,,Great. Let's fix up {\i1}Gintama \NRumble{\i0} by ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.05,0:03:46.45,Main,Shin,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! What do you think you're \Ndoing right before the release?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.96,0:03:50.43,Main,Gin,0000,0000,0000,,We're gonna do all we can to make a game \Nthat has a chance of selling a million.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.43,0:03:51.24,Main,Shin,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, right!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.24,0:03:54.34,Main,Shin,0000,0000,0000,,Do you really think we're gonna get away \Nwith sneaking in here and doing whatever?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.34,0:03:57.02,Main,Shin,0000,0000,0000,,They've almost finished \Nmaking a really fun game!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.34,0:03:59.97,sign_5808_60_Gintama_Rumble,,0000,0000,0000,,Gintama Rumble
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.02,0:03:59.97,Main,Shin,0000,0000,0000,,People with no game dev experience \Nshould keep their noses out of this!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.97,0:04:02.68,Main,Gin,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be naïve.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.68,0:04:04.96,Main,Gin,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, it might be a fun game.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.96,0:04:06.92,Main,Gin,0000,0000,0000,,But I wanna ask Bamco this:
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.92,0:04:09.23,Main,Gin,0000,0000,0000,,"Do you guys really want to score a hit?"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.23,0:04:11.94,sign_5808_60_Gintama_Rumble,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Gintama Rumble
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.68,0:04:11.94,Main,Gin,0000,0000,0000,,If they were serious about it,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.94,0:04:17.48,sign_5808_60_Gintama_Rumble,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Gintama Rumble
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.15,0:04:14.53,Main,Gin,0000,0000,0000,,this is what would happen, obviously.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.53,0:04:15.34,Main,Shin,0000,0000,0000,,Like hell!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.34,0:04:17.48,Main,Shin,0000,0000,0000,,Don't try to claw your way \Ninto a super-hit series!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.83,0:04:20.53,Main,Gin,0000,0000,0000,,There's a ton of them already, \Nso nobody'll notice if we slip ourselves in.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.53,0:04:23.77,Main,Gin,0000,0000,0000,,Can't go wrong Tales-of-ing \Nbasically anything in life.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.77,0:04:26.16,Main,Shin,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell is "Tales-of-ing"? \NWhat kinda verb is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.16,0:04:30.08,Main,Gin,0000,0000,0000,,Ignoring our crude original work is fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.51,0:04:33.43,Main,Gin,0000,0000,0000,,We're totally up for \NTales-of-ing off of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.43,0:04:36.38,Main,Shin,0000,0000,0000,,More like Tales of hitching \Na ride on their backs!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.38,0:04:38.46,Main,Shin,0000,0000,0000,,Talk about riding on \Nsomeone else's coattails!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.84,0:04:40.59,Main,Tama,0000,0000,0000,,Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.59,0:04:42.41,Main,Tama,0000,0000,0000,,You want to be carried one way or another.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.41,0:04:43.63,Main,Shin,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Tama-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.63,0:04:48.22,Main,Tama,0000,0000,0000,,So switching to a fantasy RPG, basically?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.22,0:04:51.34,Main,Shin,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a sec! What about the "Rumble" part?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.22,0:04:59.61,sign_5808_60_Gintama_Rumble,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Gintama Rumble
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.34,0:04:53.14,Main,Shin,0000,0000,0000,,That's the USP of this game, you know!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.14,0:04:57.86,Main,Kag,0000,0000,0000,,That won't be hard to work around. We can \Njust name the protag Rumble or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.86,0:04:59.61,Main,Shin,0000,0000,0000,,Who? This {\i1}will{\i0} be a {\i1}Gintama{\i0} game, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.95,0:05:05.66,Main,Gin,0000,0000,0000,,Great idea. I really hate game \Nprotags who talk too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.66,0:05:07.67,Main,Gin,0000,0000,0000,,In order to provide the best immersion,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.67,0:05:11.02,Main,Gin,0000,0000,0000,,he should say nothing but \N"yes" and "no," like in DQ.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.02,0:05:13.37,Main,Gin,0000,0000,0000,,So Gin-san doesn't have \Nto be the protag here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.75,0:05:17.52,Main,Gin,0000,0000,0000,,The protag has no personality, \Nonly speaks when required,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.15,0:05:23.13,sign_7436_88_Tales_of_Rumble,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Tales of Rumble
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.52,0:05:18.90,Main,Gin,0000,0000,0000,,and his name is Tales of Rumble.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.90,0:05:20.75,Main,Shin,0000,0000,0000,,But Rumble's dripping with personality!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.75,0:05:23.13,Main,Shin,0000,0000,0000,,Even if he doesn't say a word, \Nhis back tells the whole story!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.13,0:05:30.14,sign_7580_91_Odd_Jobs_Gin_cha,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Odd Jobs Gin-chan
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.13,0:05:30.14,sign_7580_91_Odd_Jobs_Gin_ Copy,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Snack Otose
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.64,0:05:27.25,Main,Gin,0000,0000,0000,,Rumble comes to Edo, joins Odd Jobs,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.25,0:05:30.14,Main,Gin,0000,0000,0000,,and rescues the kidnapped \Nprincess with us, is the story.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.14,0:05:33.22,Main,Shin,0000,0000,0000,,Who would self-insert \Ninto this rugged old man?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.22,0:05:35.15,Main,Shin,0000,0000,0000,,He's clearly the guy who \Nnormally kidnaps the princess!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.79,0:05:42.65,Text M,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Hello, Rumble. Welcome to Odd Jobs.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.22,0:05:42.65,Main,Gin,0000,0000,0000,,Hello, Rumble. Welcome to Odd Jobs.
